temporary files. I might consider extending `ClassLoader` to override `getResources(String name)` and possibly `loadClass`, but I’m not sure if tracking calls is necessary. I also want to ensure that `getResources` correctly returns the URL to the temp package root. I'll create actual files for `HeartbeatMessage.class` and `BranchCommitRequest.class`, as their names need to match when loading classes. If there are more than expected, I'll have to implement fallback mechanisms for managing loaded classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing ClassLoader issues**\\n\\nI’m realizing there's a potential problem with the default parent delegation in `ClassLoader.loadClass`. If I override the protected `loadClass`, it might conflict with the public inherited version. I need to ensure that the overridden `loadClass(String name)` is working as intended. The `classNameSet` will keep track of the added classes. I'm also considering whether my `getResources` override should include resources from the parent. However, the library's static initialization might only require the context class loader `getResources`. This definitely feels a bit complicated!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_50IAY3OBC0BNGmNwVl3IRtaA|fc_024dea3557175cfa0169f15f34582c81979fcba1c5be679754", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git ls-files tests/src/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/src/test/java/org_apache_seata/seata_all | head -20 && git ls-files metadata/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/reachability-metadata.json metadata/org.apache.seata/seata-all/index.json"}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"git ls-files tests/src/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/src/test/java/org_apache_seata/seata_all | head -20 && git ls-files metadata/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/reachability-metadata.json metadata/org.apache.seata/seata-all/index.json\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1620, "output": 937, "cacheRead": 20480, "cacheWrite":